ZAMFAM (TBD OVC project) is a follow-on to STEPS OVC, and will be open to local Zambian organizations interested in implementing a five-year program in Comprehensive Integrated Service Delivery and Support for Families Caring for Orphans and Vulnerable Children (OVC) and People Living with HIV (PLHIV). The project will allow for an international sub-partner which will assist the local organization
Funds allocated for Program Element HL.1.6: Adult Care and Support. All facility-based and home/community-based activities for HIV-infected adults and their families aimed at extending and optimizing quality of life for HIV-infected clients and their families throughout the continuum of illness through provision of clinical, psychological, spiritual, social and prevention services.
Funds allocated for Program Element HL.1.8: Orphans and Vulnerable Children. Activities are aimed at improving the lives of orphans and other vulnerable children (OVC) affected by HIV/AIDS, and doing so in a measurable way.
Funds allocated for Program Element HL.1.2: Sexual Prevention - Abstinence/Be Faithful. Activities (including training) to promote abstinence, fidelity, reducing multiple and concurrent partners, and related social and community norms that impact these behaviors.
Funds allocated for Program Element HL.1.17: Pediatric Care and Support. All health facility-based care for HIV-exposed children and their families aimed at extending and optimizing quality of life for HIV-infected clients and their families throughout the continuum of illness through provision of clinical, psychological, spiritual, social and prevention services.
objectives</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">ZAMFAM (TBD OVC project) is a follow-on to STEPS OVC, and will be open to local Zambian organizations interested in implementing a five-year program in Comprehensive Integrated Service Delivery and Support for Families Caring for Orphans and Vulnerable Children (OVC) and People Living with HIV (PLHIV). The project will allow for an international sub-partner which will assist the local organizations in organizational development and other duties as identified during the organization&#x2019;s assessment process.  
The purpose of the project is to improve outcomes through support to implement comprehensive and coordinated evidence-based interventions that strengthen the capacity of families and communities to care for their vulnerable children in Central and Southern Provinces of Zambia. This project will contribute to the improved care and support for people living/affected by HIV/AIDS, and strengthen the organizational and technical capacity of local organizations and community structures to mitigate the HIV/AIDS impact.  
This activity will contribute to the achievement of the USAID/Zambia Mission Country Development Cooperative Strategy&#x2019;s (CDCS), Development Objective 2, Rural Poverty Reduced in Targeted Areas and Development Objective 3, Human Capital Improved, by reducing the impact of HIV/AIDS on vulnerable households through a multi-sector response. The award will reach approximately 125,105 OVC per year for five years and is estimated to have a LOP amount between $20 million and $24 million.

This TBD was originally part of the TBD: Comprehensive Integrated Service Delivery and Support for Families Care for OVC and PLHIV (16634) which has been split into three mechanisms including Project SOAR (17833).</narrative>
  </description>
